description: Sebi chairperson Madhabi Buch is to appear before the Public Accounts Committee (PAC) of Parliament on Thursday for a performance review. Despite BJP's protest, she will address questions linked to allegations of financial misconduct and conflict of interest amid political tensions. Buch had sought an exemption from the PAC but was denied.
title: Denied exemption, Sebi chief Madhabi Buch set to appear before PAC tomorrow

description: India and Singapore have agreed to deepen defence cooperation by commencing co-development and co-production of military equipment, and extending their joint military training agreement for five more years. The countries aim to enhance defence-industry collaboration, particularly in automation and AI, while boosting cyber security cooperation amidst increasing regional challenges.
title: Eye on China, India steps up defence ties with Singapore

description: Six family members, including a pregnant woman and a toddler, died, and two others were critically injured when an oxygen cylinder exploded in their house in Sikandrabad, Bulandshahr. The blast flattened the two-storey house and caused tremors felt 500 meters away. Authorities are providing medical care to the injured.
title: Oxygen cylinder blast flattens 2-storey UP house, kills 6 of family

description: C-60 commando Kumod Atram, who has been part of 22 encounters over eight years, recounted his recent experience in a battle against Maoist guerrillas where he sustained three gunshot injuries. Atram's team killed five PLGA fighters during this operation aimed at preventing disruptions in the Nov 20 Maharashtra polls.
title: 'Ab tak unchaalis...' and counting for injured anti-Maoist commando

description: Mumbai police linked Baba Siddique's murder to jailed gangster Lawrence Bishnoi, identifying three shooters who communicated with Bishnoi's cousin in Canada before the crime. Two shooters are in custody, with the third on the run. Police are uncovering layers of conspirators.
title: 'Baba Siddique shooters, Bishnoi cousin spoke before murder'
Biren failed to restore peace, axe him, Meitei group tells PM

description: Both BJP and the Eknath Shinde-led Shiv Sena are keen to contest the Worli assembly seat, currently held by Aaditya Thackeray of Sena (UBT). BJP's Shaina N C and MNS's Sandeep Deshpande have shown interest, while Sena plans to field a local candidate.
title: Both BJP, Sena keen to take on Aaditya Thackeray in Worli
NGT notices to Centre, states on study linking deaths to pollution

description: Lois Marandi's exit from BJP to join JMM has created turmoil within BJP, particularly in fielding a credible candidate against Hemant Soren in Barhait. Marandi, after two decades with BJP, is speculated to be contesting from Jama constituency. BJP's Himanta Biswa Sarma claims they have multiple options for Barhait, yet no decision has been announced.
title: Marandi out, BJP hunts for Hemant Soren den pick

description: A consumer in Chennai received a 2999900% return after a post office was ordered to refund 50 paise with a Rs 15,000 fine due to rounding off transactions. The commission deemed this practice an unfair trade practice under the Consumer Protection Act, 2019.
title: Post office fined Rs 15,000 for not returning 50 paise to man

description: In an effort to diminish the status of absconding criminals, Uttarakhand police announced a symbolic reward of Rs 5 for their capture. This move follows a violent shootout in Jafarpur village involving three wanted offenders. Posters will be circulated to facilitate their arrest.
title: Cops' Rs 5 reward on 3 goons 'to show their true worth'
Contract staff to get maternity benefits too: Madras HC

description: India and Pakistan have agreed to extend the validity of the Kartarpur Sahib corridor agreement for another five years, ensuring uninterrupted access for Indian pilgrims to Gurdwara Darbar Sahib in Pakistan. This decision follows EAM S Jaishankar's visit to Islamabad for the SCO meeting. Both nations underscore their commitment to fostering interfaith harmony and peaceful coexistence.
title: India, Pakistan to extend Kartarpur corridor pact for 5 more years

description: A special NIA court in Guwahati framed charges against Assam MLA Akhil Gogoi and three others under UAPA and IPC for their roles in violent protests against the CAA in 2019. Charges related to sedition and support for a terrorist organization were dropped. The accused plan to challenge these charges in the high court.
title: Assam MLA charged under UAPA over protests against CAA in 2019

description: General Upendra Dwivedi highlighted efforts towards restoring trust between India and China following their new 'patrolling arrangements' agreement in eastern Ladakh. He emphasized that trust restoration could lead to troop disengagement and de-escalation. However, concerns remain over China's intentions, with cautions against allowing a repeat of Doklam's strategic standoff and infrastructure buildup by China.
title: We are trying to restore trust, says General after LAC agreement
Another 50 bomb threats take number of flights hit to 170+
Fake arbitrator of fake tribunal lands behind bars in Gujarat

description: US secretary of state Antony Blinken meets Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, urging capitalisation on Hamas leader Yahaya Sinwar's death for a Gaza ceasefire and increased humanitarian aid. Blinken emphasises the need for lasting security and clarifies Israel's intentions amid ongoing conflict and dire humanitarian conditions in northern Gaza.
title: Blinken urges Netanyahu to 'capitalise' on Sinwar death and work towards Gaza ceasefire

description: Odisha is preparing to evacuate up to 10 lakh people due to the severe cyclonic storm Dana, with potential landfall in Kendrapara district. Over 6,000 shelters are ready, and extensive rescue and relief teams are deployed. Schools and government offices will remain closed, and rescue operations are being closely monitored by senior officials and local lawmakers.
title: Cyclone landfall likely tomorrow, Odisha to evacuate 10 lakh

description: After intensive discussions, a seat-sharing consensus for the Maharashtra Assembly elections has been reached: Congress will contest 105 seats, UBT Shiv Sena 95, and Sharad Pawar's NCP the remaining. The arrangement followed intervention by Congress leaders, though disputes over some Mumbai seats remain unresolved.
title: MVA pact: Congress 105, UBT Sena 95, Sharad's NCP 84
3 dead, 7 feared trapped in Bengaluru building collapse

description: Ripudaman Singh Malik, accused in the 1985 Air India bombing but later acquitted, was murdered by local criminals Tanner Fox and Jose Lopez. Their guilty plea highlights a gangland killing linked to disputes involving Sikh community members, including slain terrorist Hardeep Singh Nijjar with local tensions around religious and legal conflicts.
title: 2 plead guilty to murder of Sikh businessman cleared in Air India bombing

description: BJP MP Pradeep Kumar Singh's statement in Araria, suggesting non-Hindus can't live there, sparked controversy. Singh urged unity under Hindu identity, contradicting ally JD(U) and facing criticism from RJD. BJP defended it as a stance against illegal immigrants.
title: Have to be Hindu to live in Araria, says Bihar BJP MLA at Giriraj rally

description: During his first bilateral meeting with Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian, PM Narendra Modi expressed concerns over the escalating West Asia conflict and stressed the importance of dialogue and diplomacy. According to an Indian readout, Modi also emphasised on protection of civilians and the role of diplomacy in resolving the conflict.
title: Modi talks West Asia conflict at first meet with Iran president
J&K crackdown: Terror recruitment module busted after raids in 7 districts

description: PM Modi and President Putin emphasized peaceful resolution of the Russia-Ukraine conflict during their bilateral meeting. Modi highlighted India's ongoing diplomatic efforts and the humanitarian priority while Putin acknowledged the strategic partnership. Modi last met Putin in Moscow in July when he visited Moscow for the annual India-Russia summit mechanism after a gap of two years.
title: India ready to back peace efforts, PM Modi tells Putin

description: In a daring operation, Capt Reena Varughese piloted a Dauphin-N Pawan Hans chopper into the Maoist stronghold of Abujmarh to rescue a wounded C-60 commando. Facing the risk of mortar attack, she jumped from the hovering chopper onto rocky terrain, highlighting bravery in the eight-hour siege that resulted in five Maoists being killed.
title: Daring woman copter pilot saves wounded commando

description: India confirms a bilateral meeting between PM Modi and President Xi Jinping on the sidelines of the Brics summit in Russia. This follows a recent agreement on LAC patrolling, aiming to return to the situation in 2020. Both nations indicate readiness to implement the solution efficiently.
title: 5 years after their last bilateral, Modi-Xi meet in Russia today

description: The Uttar Pradesh government argued before the Supreme Court to retain madrassas and reform their education system, challenging Allahabad High Court’s verdict against the UP Board of Madarsa Education Act, 2004. The Supreme Court emphasized the importance of mainstreaming madrassa education and incorporating subjects like math and science.
title: Yogi govt says HC wrong in quashing madrassa law, but it accepted verdict

description: India's Test squad for the Australian tour will likely be announced on October 28, with veteran Cheteshwar Pujara a potential inclusion due to his past performances in Australia and current form. Pujara last played for India in the World Test Championship final in 2023. The selection panel will also make a decision on Mohammed Shami's inclusion.
title: India's squad for Australia tour likely on Oct 28, Pujara in the fray

description: WhatsApp is introducing features to manage contacts from any device, starting with WhatsApp Web and Windows. Users can now save contacts exclusively within WhatsApp, separate from the device's contact list. The update paves the way for a future username system, enhancing privacy by eliminating the need to share phone numbers.
title: WhatsApp is solving this ‘big’ contacts problem with new features

description: Farooq Abdullah blames Pakistan for increased terrorism in J&K, demanding a halt to killings before any talks. The recent attack in Ganderbal killed seven workers, prompting PDP's Mehbooba Mufti to call for ensuring migrant workers' safety amidst rising fear and panic among them.
title: Farooq blames Pakistan, says no talks until killings stop
Maharashtra elections: Eknath Shinde's Sena releases 1st list of candidates

description: Canadian MPs held an emergency debate on foreign interference, alleging the Indian government’s involvement in crimes against Canadian Sikhs. Calls were made for the RSS to be designated a terrorist organization, sanctions against India, and stricter measures on entry for BJP officials linked to violence.
title: NDP calls for India sanctions, ban on RSS in Canada

description: Six of Sean "Diddy" Comb's children declared their father's innocence on social media, following accusations of sex trafficking and racketeering. They labeled the allegations as baseless. Diddy, who pleaded not guilty, remains in jail awaiting trial next year. Several high-profile associates have also been implicated.
title: Sean 'Diddy' Combs's kids slam allegations and conspiracy theories

description: The IMF projects India's GDP growth to moderate from 8.2% in 2023 to 7% in 2024 and 6.5% in 2025 as post-pandemic demand depletes. Headline inflation is expected to fall to 3.5% by end of 2025. Finance minister Nirmala Sitharaman remains optimistic, stating India is on track to become the third largest economy by 2027.
title: IMF says India's GDP growth to moderate to 7% in 2024 and 6.5% in 2025

description: Three gunmen, involved in the murder of NCP leader Baba Siddique, practiced shooting near a waterfall in Raigad, Mumbai police revealed. Initially part of a larger contract killing module, they trained in Palasdhari, Karjat. So far, ten arrests have been made, but key individuals remain at large. Various motives are under investigation.
title: Shooters held target practice before shooting Baba Siddique, say cops

description: Bigg Boss 18 contestant Hema Sharma addresses allegations made by her estranged husband Gaurav Saxena, stating he struggles to accept her success after abandoning her. She clarifies that his claims are false and motivated by his desire for fame. Further legal discussion is planned.
title: Exclusive - Bigg Boss 18's Hema Sharma reacts to second husband's allegations

description: Five people were killed and several injured in a shooting at a football match in Jamaica, according to police. The shooting occurred in the capital of Kingston late on Monday during a friendly game, police told reporters.
title: Tragedy during football match! Gunfire leaves 5 dead

description: During a meeting at the BRICS Summit, Iranian President Masoud Pezeshkian emphasised India's potential role in mitigating Middle East tensions, while PM Narendra Modi reiterated the importance of dialogue and civilian protection. Discussions also included Afghanistan's stability and continued humanitarian aid.
title: In meet with PM Modi, Iran prez stresses India’s role in resolving Middle East tensions

description: A 23-year-old woman, Matilda Campbell, was rescued after getting trapped upside down in a narrow crevice between boulders in Australia's Hunter Valley. The operation took seven hours and required a multidisciplinary team effort. Campbell remained calm throughout and was freed with minor injuries. She later shared her experience humorously on social media.
title: Woman wedged upside down between boulders for 7 hours after trying to retrieve phone

description: Maharashtra Navnirman Sena released a list of 45 candidates for the upcoming state assembly elections on November 20. Raj Thackeray's son Amit will debut from Mahim, while Sandeep Deshpande will contest from Worli against Aaditya Thackeray. Votes will be counted on November 23, amid significant recent political shifts in the state.
title: Maha polls: MNS releases list of 45 names, Raj Thackeray's son to make debut

description: Three workers died and three remained trapped after a building collapse in Bengaluru amidst heavy rains. Fourteen others were rescued. The downpour caused significant flooding, with authorities deploying rescue teams. Opposition parties criticized the ruling government, while several areas faced traffic jams and pothole issues.
title: Watch: 7-storey building collapses in Bengaluru amid heavy rains

description: Over 170 flights in India have been affected by bomb threats in the past nine days, resulting in an estimated Rs 600 crore loss for airlines. These threats, majorly communicated through social media, caused significant disruptions. Authorities are now considering legislative measures and tighter security protocols to prevent such incidents in the future.
title: Hoax bomb threats: Rs 600 crore loss estimated for airlines in 9 days

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will hold bilateral talks with Chinese President Xi Jinping at the BRICS summit on October 23, following a new agreement on patrolling arrangements along the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in areas of eastern Ladakh, marking their first formal discussion in five years. PM Modi last met Xi Jinping in 2019 on the sidelines of the Shanghai Cooperation Organisation (SCO) summit in Kyrgyzstan's Bishkek and discussed ways to further strengthen the bilateral relations.
title: PM Modi to hold talks with Xi on sidelines of Brics; first meet in 5 years
Maha muddle: Mahayuti, MVA struggle to break seat-sharing impasse

description: A Joint Parliamentary Committee meeting turned chaotic when TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee smashed a glass bottle and hurled it at BJP's Jagdambika Pal, leading to Banerjee's suspension for one session. The scuffle ensued after Banerjee spoke out of turn during discussions on the Waqf bill.
title: 'Glass bottle smashed, abuses hurled': Inside chaotic JPC meet on Waqf bill

description: There are growing calls for President Mohammed Shahabuddin's resignation in Bangladesh following his controversial remarks on deposed Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina. Protests led by the Anti-discrimination Student Movement and other groups demand Shahabuddin step down and the dissolution of Hasina's Awami League party. Shahabuddin claims he has no documentary proof of Hasina's resignation.
title: Protesters call for Bangladesh president's removal over remarks on Hasina

description: Former Pakistan batsman Basit Ali advises PCB selector Aaqib Javed to not wait anymore to announce the squad for the Australia tour, while also warning him of potential opposition within the Pakistan board. Basit emphasizes support for Fakhar Zaman, who may face sanctions for backing ex-captain Babar Azam.
title: 'Chocolaty miyan, Pakistan team announce kar do yaar'

description: TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee vows to continue fighting non-secular forces after losing his temper and injuring his hand during a heated Waqf Board JPC meeting. He was suspended for a day after an altercation with BJP MPs, where he broke a glass bottle and sustained injuries. The Waqf (Amendment) Bill, 2024 aims to implement reforms by introducing digitization, stricter audits, transparency, and legal measures to reclaim illegally occupied properties.
title: 'I'll keep fighting ... ': TMC's Kalyan Banerjee losing cool in Waqf meet

description: India and Pakistan have mutually agreed to extend the validity of the Kartarpur Sahib Corridor agreement by five years, ensuring uninterrupted travel for Indian pilgrims to the holy Gurdwara in Pakistan. India also continues to urge Pakistan to waive the $20 service charge for visiting pilgrims.
title: India-Pak extend validity of agreement on Kartarpur corridor by 5 years

description: Ukraine's population has sharply declined by over 10 million due to the ongoing conflict since February 2022, according to the United Nations. The war has led to a significant exodus of citizens and a plunging birth rate, now one of the lowest globally. Current population figures stand at approximately 37.86 million, a significant drop from 2022.
title: 10 million people wiped from Ukraine's population since the Russian invasion: UN

description: Dive into the top five entertainment stories of the day, where we bring you the latest buzz straight from the world of movies, celebrities, and pop culture. From Mika Singh supporting Salman Khan amid threats from Lawrence Bishnoi to Shraddha Kapoor on Stree 2 beating Pathaan and Jawan to Somy Ali sharing Priyanka Chopra's video; here's taking a look at top FIVE news from the world of entertainment today!
title: Mika Singh supporting Salman Khan and other entertainment news

description: On October 22, the government launched the 'International Incoming Spoofed Calls Prevention System' to block international calls disguised as Indian numbers. This system aims to protect citizens from financial scams, impersonations, and cyber-crime by identifying and blocking such spoofed calls. Within 24 hours, it blocked about 1.35 crore calls, ensuring a safer digital space.
title: Govt launches system to block ‘fake’ international scam calls

description: Hockey has been excluded from the 2026 Commonwealth Games in Glasgow to cut costs. Hosts Glasgow limited the Games to 10 sports, affecting hockey and others. For Indian athletes, this impacts a significant preparation platform for major events and government jobs. The Federation of International Hockey (FIH) clarified that the decision to not include the sport in Glasgow was a one-off.
title: 'Absence of hockey at CWG is not a good sign': Rupinder

description: A Bengaluru woman's ex-boyfriend allegedly used his job at a food delivery platform to track her location by flagging her account after their breakup. He monitored her movements and questioned her activities, making her realize he was stalking her through the app. The LinkedIn post detailing the incident has sparked debates on privacy breaches.
title: Account flagged and more: Here is "The Most Traumatizing Bumble dating app Story"

description: Congress leader Priyanka Gandhi Vadra will officially enter the Wayanad by-election race on October 23, with her nomination. Supported by senior leaders, including Rahul Gandhi and Sonia Gandhi, Priyanka's candidacy aims to maintain strong representation for the people of Wayanad.
title: Team Gandhi travels to Wayanad for Priyanka Gandhi's bypoll nomination

description: Vinesh Phogat dismissed allegations by Sakshi Malik claiming their protest against former WFI chief Brij Bhushan Singh was driven by greed. Phogat defended their actions, highlighting their dedication to the cause and the sport. Malik, however, argued that accepted exemptions from Asian Games trials compromised the movement's credibility.
title: 'Will carry this greed till death': Vinesh Phogat on Sakshi Malik's allegations

description: Debina Bonnerjee and Gurmeet Choudhary hosted Farah Khan for a food vlog, where Debina cooked the Bengali dish Shukto. The trio reminisced about their time on Nach Baliye. They discussed parenting challenges, with Farah sharing her experience raising triplets and their shared IVF journey, including the emotional and physical tolls of failed attempts.
title: Debina Bonnerjee and Farah Khan recall IVF journeys and taking care of kids

description: Entrepreneurship has experienced remarkable growth in India, emerging as a vital driver of economic and social development. The GUESSS India 2023 Report highlights that 32% of students aspire to start their own ventures, showcasing a strong entrepreneurial spirit among youth. Factors such as increased access to entrepreneurial education, government support, and digital tools have further fueled this trend, making it an attractive career path for many young individuals.
title: 32.5% of Indian students aim to be startup owners: 5 reasons driving ambitions

description: Eight teenagers in Sarajevo have been arrested for making numerous fake bomb threats to schools, disrupting classes since early October. Police inspections and evacuations have been routine. Among those arrested, seven are minors, and one is 18. Under Bosnian law, they could face up to five years in prison if found guilty.
title: Sarajevo bomb scare: Police arrest eight teens after several fake threats

description: The Communist Party of India (CPI) declared its candidates for the Jharkhand assembly elections, citing dissatisfaction with seat allocations offered by the INDIA bloc allies. The CPI plans to contest 15 seats independently, criticizing CM Hemant Soren's government for disappointing the youth over the past five years. The Jharkhand Assembly elections will be held in two phases on November 13 and November 20 and votes will be counted on November 23.
title: CPI breaks ranks with INDIA bloc in Jharkhand, to go solo in assembly polls

description: Pakistan's Test team coach Jason Gillespie was seen picking up empty bottles, presumably left by players after a training session, ahead of the crucial third Test against England in Rawalpindi. Social media users praised Gillespie's humility. The ground staff are working hard to dry the pitch to favour Pakistan spinners after their series-levelling win in Multan.
title: 'Hats off, Mr Gillespie': Pakistan coach cleans up litter

description: The West Bengal government has ordered the closure of schools, colleges, and ICDS centers in nine districts from October 23 to 25, 2024, due to Cyclone Dana. Ferry services will also be suspended. The India Meteorological Department (IMD) predicts heavy rainfall in West Bengal and Odisha as the cyclone intensifies. Safety precautions are advised.
title: Bengal schools closed from Oct 23 to 25 due to cyclone Dana: Check details here

description: In 2012, scientists conducted a controlled crash of a Boeing 727 to determine the safest seating locations during a plane crash. The study found that passengers at the back had the highest survival chances, while those at the front were at the greatest risk. The experiment emphasized adopting the brace position to minimize injuries.
title: How to survive plane crash? Insights from scientists who crashed a Boeing

description: Ahead of the second Test against New Zealand, former teammates Virat Kohli and Gautam Gambhir were seen sharing light moments during a net session in Pune. Meanwhile, Team India remains hopeful about Rishabh Pant's recovery from his knee injury. Sarfaraz Khan's performance in the previous Test creates a selection dilemma.
title: Kohli, Gambhir share light moments during net session

description: Investor losses reached Rs 9.19 lakh crore as Sensex and Nifty50 indices fell sharply due to large foreign fund outflows and weak global equities. Sensex dropped 930.55 points to 80,220.72, while Nifty50 fell 309 points to 24,472.10 amid investor concerns and valuation adjustments.
title: Market crash: D-street investors poorer by Rs 9.19 lakh crore in a day

description: Prime Minister Modi attends the 16th Brics summit in Kazan, focusing on inclusivity and expanded member cooperation. The group now includes Egypt, Ethiopia, Iran, and the UAE, aiming to challenge the Western-led global order, particularly the dominance of the US dollar. Internal dynamics and divergent national interests present ongoing challenges for cohesive action.
title: PM Modi in Russia: What all to know about Brics and why it matters

description: After Samantha Ruth Prabhu and Naga Chaitanya announced their divorce in 2021, the narrative around their separation shifted when Naga got engaged to Sobhita Dhulipala in 2024. The article highlights how each individual handled the situation, emphasizing integrity, respect, and personal growth.
title: A take away from Samantha, Naga Chaitanya, and Sobhita's relationship triangle

description: At a campaign stop in Michigan, Vice President Kamala Harris made it clear that she doesn’t use marijuana edibles to manage stress, responding humorously to a comment about gummies from Maria Shriver. Harris acknowledged feeling tension as the election nears, sharing that she wakes up at night but copes by working out each morning. While not using edibles herself, she supports federal marijuana legalization, with Michigan being one of the states where recreational use is legal.
title: Is Kamala Harris eating marijuana gummies to relax during election season?

description: New Zealand are optimistic following their impressive eight-wicket win over India in the rain-affected first Test in Bengaluru. Despite India's expected strong comeback, Kiwi batsman Daryl Mitchell asserts his team's readiness to tackle diverse challenges in Pune, including varying spin conditions.
title: 'One thing we can't do is...' - NZ ready for wounded India

description: In Hyderabad, a 22-year-old painter, Gayapu Uday Kiran, fell from a hotel's third floor and died while playfully chasing a dog in the corridor. The accident, captured on CCTV, occurred during a birthday party with friends. Uday was declared dead at a private hospital. Police have registered a case and initiated an investigation following a complaint from the victim's father.
title: Video: Chasing dog, man falls off 3rd floor in Hyderabad, dies

description: David Warner, former Australian opener, is ready for a Test cricket return for the Border-Gavaskar Trophy against India. Having retired, Warner now offers to fill Australia's opening slot amid current team challenges. He emphasized his seriousness, having contacted head coach and selectors, showcasing his eagerness and potential to strengthen Australia's batting lineup.
title: 'I’m always available, just...': Warner drops a bombshell ahead of India series
Under-construction building collapses in Bengaluru, several feared trapped

description: Indian badminton gurus Pullela Gopichand and Vimal Kumar express disapproval over the exclusion of key sports, including badminton, from the 2026 Glasgow Commonwealth Games. They argue that such decisions hinder India's progress and advocate for focusing on the Olympics and Asian Games instead.
title: 'India shouldn't send team for Commonwealth Games'

description: Nearly 50 flights have received threats on Tuesday, with a notable increase in such incidents. IndiGo and Air India reported multiple threats, leading to diversions and heightened security measures. Authorities are working to identify and punish those responsible for these threats, ensuring passenger safety.
title: Fresh bomb threats for about 50 flights; 3 international flights diverted

description: The father of the deceased trainee doctor from RG Kar Medical College sought help from Union Minister Amit Shah, citing tremendous mental pressure and a pursuit of justice. In an email, the victim's father wrote, "I am (the) father of Abhaya and I am writing to respectfully request an appointment with you at your convenience or at any other location as you may suggest."
title: 'Tremendous mental pressure': RG Kar victim's father writes to Amit Shah

description: Trinamool Congress defended Kalyan Banerjee after a scuffle with BJP's Abhijit Gangopadhyay during the Joint Parliamentary Committee meet on the Waqf Bill. Banerjee was suspended for one day. The incident arose amidst tensions over the consultative process and allegations of political motives behind the bill.
title: 'Person with huge nuisance value': TMC defends Banerjee after scuffle with BJP MP

description: Ahead of the Brics summit, PM Modi and President Putin held talks with PM Modi stressing India’s commitment to peace in the Russia-Ukraine conflict. The summit aims to strengthen Brics' push for a multipolar world order, challenging Western dominance in global affairs. ​​Speaking on the Russia-Ukraine war, PM Modi said India will fully support the early establishment of peace and stability.
title: Watch: 'I felt that ... ': Putin's remark makes PM Modi burst into laughter

description: Mercedes-Benz India launched the all-new Mercedes-AMG G 63 at Rs 3.60 crore, featuring a 4.0-litre V8 bi-turbo engine, 48V mild hybrid tech, and advanced suspension for optimal performance. Boasting Nappa leather upholstery, an MBUX NTG7 system, and extensive customization options, deliveries are set for Q3 2025.
title: Mercedes-AMG G63 facelift launched at Rs 3.60 crore: 0-100 kmph in 4.3 seconds!

description: Dismissed police officer Sachin Waze receives bail in a corruption case linked to ex-Maharashtra home minister Anil Deshmukh. Waze alleges Deshmukh pressured him into illegal activities and that the home's ministry work quality declined under Deshmukh's leadership. Waze had been jailed since March 2021.
title: Ex-cop Sachin Waze gets bail in corruption case involving Anil Deshmukh

description: Donald Trump's connection with WWE spans over three decades, featuring his induction into the WWE Hall of Fame and appearance in the 'Battle of the Billionaires.' WWE legends like Hulk Hogan and The Undertaker have shown support for Trump's 2024 presidential campaign, which could influence public perception and sway voter decisions.
title: Donald Trump engaging WWE Legends for US Presidential Elections: Exploring reasons

description: The Supreme Court has reserved its decision on the appeals challenging the Allahabad High Court's ruling that declared the Uttar Pradesh Board of Madarsa Education Act, 2004 unconstitutional. The ruling found it violated secularism principles, and the Supreme Court provided temporary relief to madrasa students. Various senior advocates argued for the petitioners over two days.
title: Madarsa Education Act: SC reserves order on appeals against HC's ruling

description: Ajmal Sultan, an autorickshaw driver in Bengaluru, has launched an initiative called 'Learn Kannada With Auto Kannadiga' by placing posters in his auto that provide Kannada-to-English phrase translations.
title: "Let's fix the language problem in Bengaluru," the auto driver Aslam's post viral
Two coaches of CMST Shalimar Express derail near Maharashtra's Nagpur

description: With the 5 November election nearing, Harlan Ullman, senior advisor at the Atlantic Council, questioned whether President Joe Biden would have been a stronger candidate than Vice President Kamala Harris, given her recent struggles. Ullman suggested Biden's experience may have served America better, despite concerns over his age. While Harris initially had momentum, Donald Trump has closed the gap. Ullman highlighted Biden's strengths, though his physical decline raised doubts. Meanwhile, Trump's energetic presence continues to resonate, contrasting with Harris' campaign challenges.
title: Why iconic strategist thinks Harris is worse than Biden

description: Team India is determined to bounce back in the second Test against New Zealand in Pune after an eight-wicket loss in Bengaluru. With Washington Sundar joining the squad and Shubman Gill and Rishabh Pant fit, focus shifts to Sarfaraz Khan and KL Rahul vying for a place in the playing eleven.
title: 'It's Sarfaraz vs Rahul': Focus on playing XI as India aim to bounce back

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi's bilateral talks with Russian President Vladimir Putin on the sidelines of the Brics summit emphasized strengthening Indo-Russian relations, addressing the Russia-Ukraine conflict peacefully, and India opening a new consulate in Kazan. The Brics summit focuses on promoting a multipolar world order and enhancing global economic discussions. Brics represents a significant portion of the world’s population and economic output.
title: 'Priority to humanity': Key quotes from PM Modi-Putin bilateral meet

description: Charges under the Unlawful Activities (Prevention) Act have been framed against Assam MLA Akhil Gogoi and his associates for their role in anti-Citizenship Amendment Act protests. Some charges, including sedition, were dropped. Gogoi condemned the government's actions, vowing to fight the case in Gauhati High Court.
title: NIA frames charges against Assam MLA Akhil Gogoi under UAPA for anti-CAA stir

description: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg hosted a 70s-themed disco party for his wife, Priscilla Chan. Clad in sparkling outfits, the couple celebrated with a lively crowd. Zuckerberg humorously interacted with followers, sharing insights about their relationship and life.
title: Tech industry's ‘Shah Jahan’ throws party for disco queen

description: The Bombay high court has denied pre-arrest bail to Akash Avhad, accused of assaulting a 71-year-old man on suspicion of carrying beef. The court emphasized that Avhad's custodial interrogation is essential for the ongoing investigation, which involves serious charges including hurting religious sentiments. The victim man registered a case at Thane police station.
title: No court relief for man who thrashed 71 y/o over suspicion of carrying beef

description: With Delhi's pollution levels worsening, Environment Minister Gopal Rai has introduced measures like additional metro trips, 6,200 MCD workers for road dust control, and 1,800 extra traffic personnel. GRAP Stage II restrictions include intensified inspections and a 'Red Light On-Gaadi Off' campaign to curb vehicle emissions. Urgent steps are being taken to address the rising AQI.
title: 'Don't send diesel buses to Delhi': Gopal Rai to neighbouring states on air pollution

description: A video clip of Shriver’s exchange soon went viral on social media, leading to widespread criticism. Many users remarked that the event appeared more like a staged production rather than a genuine town hall, where candidates typically engage with unscripted questions from voters. Comments on X (formerly Twitter) were filled with scepticism, with one user remarking that the event resembled a "stage production" rather than an authentic town hall, claiming that Harris was unable to handle spontaneous interactions.
title: No questions please: Kamala Harris mocked for holding 'staged' townhall

description: NASA confirms asteroid 363305 (2002 NV16), about 580 feet wide, will pass Earth safely on October 24, 2024, at 4.52 million kilometres away. Though labelled as potentially hazardous, there's no danger. NASA continuously monitors such threats, demonstrating preparedness with missions like the DART to ensure Earth's safety from future asteroid impacts.
title: Nasa alert! 580-feet asteroid set to pass by Earth on October 24, 2024

description: Meta CEO Mark Zuckerberg hosted a 70s-themed disco party for his wife, Priscilla Chan. Clad in sparkling outfits, the couple celebrated with a lively crowd. Zuckerberg humorously interacted with followers, sharing insights about their relationship and life.
title: ‘Shah Jahan’ throws party for disco queen

description: Karan Johar addresses speculations of using Ozempic for his significant weight loss, crediting healthy eating and nutrition instead. Amidst rising popularity, experts warn against Ozempic's off-label use for weight loss due to side effects and supply issues for diabetes patients. Dr. Anjali Hooda emphasizes the necessity of lifestyle changes alongside medication.
title: B-town using Ozempic for rapid weight loss? Celeb nutritionist's warning

description: Shubman Gill, the prominent Indian batter, is fit to participate in the second Test match against New Zealand after recovering from an injury.
title: Shubman Gill boost for India ahead of 2nd Test vs New Zealand in Pune

description: Rishabh Pant, recovering from a knee injury and a near-fatal car accident, is expected to keep wickets in Pune's 2nd Test against New Zealand. Despite discomfort and injections, Pant's return is backed by the team management. The BCCI medical team is confident he will overcome the injury and be fit for the upcoming match.
title: Team India assistant coach gives big update on Rishabh Pant's fitness

description: Nobel laureate Paul Romer praised India's Aadhaar as a groundbreaking technological innovation, transforming government services and direct benefit transfers. Romer noted India's proactive use of Aadhaar, contrasting it with Western legal and corporate barriers. He emphasized the necessity of urban development for economic growth and urged India to assert its sovereignty amid rising geopolitical tensions.
title: Nobel prize winner on Western countries 'failure' to build system like Aadhaar

description: Exuding confidence over the candidature of Congress leader Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, Lok Sabha Leader of Opposition Rahul Gandhi on Tuesday said that she will emerge as a passionate champion of Wayanad's needs and a powerful voice in Parliament.
title: 'Priyanka will be passionate champion of Wayanad's needs': Rahul Gandhi
Waqf Bill: TMC's Banerjee smashes glass bottle after altercation with BJP MP during JPC meet

description: China and India have reached a resolution on their disputed border, agreeing on military patrols along the Line of Actual Control. This deal aims to disengage troops and restore peace along the frontier. The announcements precede a BRICS summit in Russia, fueling speculation of potential talks between Chinese President Xi Jinping and Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi.
title: 'In close communication': China's 1st statement on LAC agreement with India

description: In an unusual ruling by the MP High Court, Faizal Nisar, accused of raising anti-India slogans, has been granted bail under the condition of saluting the national flag and chanting 'Bharat Mata ki Jai' at a police station in Jabalpur regularly until his trial concludes.
title: Punishment for 'Pak Zindabad' slogan: MP man made to do 21 salutes; watch video

description: Delhi's air pollution has led to a 15% rise in respiratory illnesses. The AQI dropped to the 'very poor' category, prompting special OPD services for pollution-related ailments. Doctors emphasize using N95 masks and staying indoors. Key pollution hotspots include Narela and Rohini, with government plans to curb pollution through various initiatives.
title: Why Delhi's air pollution is more dangerous than you think

description: Over 2.7 lakh Vistara passengers who booked flights for travel after Nov 12, 2024, are migrated to Air India reservations. Tata Group ensures continuity in travel experience while enhancing the digital arena with a one-click booking feature and upgraded digital tools.
title: ‘Over 2.7 lakh Vistara bookings for travel after Nov 12 migrated to Air India’

description: Joe Root has the potential to surpass Sachin Tendulkar's record as the highest run scorer in Test cricket, says former England captain Alastair Cook. Root recently became England's top Test scorer, surpassing Cook with a current total of 12,716 runs. Cook believes Root could become the first player to score 16,000 Test runs.
title: Can Root break Tendulkar's record? Alastair Cook gives his verdict

description: Ahead of Maharashtra elections, BJP member Vishwabnadhu Rai has put up posters in various parts of Mumbai with UP Chief Minister Yogi Adityanath’s image and the slogan 'Batenge to Katenge.' The slogan underscores the call for national unity to avoid the consequences of societal divisions.
title: Posters of UP CM Yogi's 'Batenge to Katenge' slogan create buzz in Mumbai

description: Australian captain Pat Cummins identifies Rishabh Pant as India's 'X-factor' in the upcoming five-match Test series starting November 22 in Perth. Cummins expresses determination to overturn Australia's four-series losing streak against India, despite notable absences such as Cameron Green due to injury. It will be the first five-match Test series between Australia and India since 1992.
title: Border Gavaskar Trophy: Pat Cummins identifies Team India's 'X-factor'

description: The Supreme Court has halted demolition actions in Uttar Pradesh until tomorrow amidst communal tensions after the Bahraich violence on October 13. Five arrests have been made, with demolition notices challenged by accused individuals arguing punitive motives. The court has yet to rule on the petition.
title: No demolition related to Bahraich violence till next hearing: UP govt assures SC

description: Army chief General Upendra Dwivedi announced India's desire to revert to the April 2020 status quo along the Line of Actual Control with China. Following extensive negotiations, India and China have agreed to return to pre-Galwan clash patrolling arrangements in eastern Ladakh, including Depsang and Demchok areas, ending a 54-month-long military standoff.
title: 'Trying to restore trust': Army chief reacts to India-China LAC deal

description: Facing challenges in securing a ceasefire in Gaza, Israeli entrepreneurs, like former SodaStream CEO Daniel Birnbaum, are offering financial incentives to release hostages. Birnbaum has pledged $100,000 for each freed Israeli prisoner, hoping civilians with captive information will act. Efforts include raising significant funds and distributing flyers, though many question the effectiveness of these attempts.
title: Israeli entrepreneurs offer cash rewards to free Gaza hostages

description: India has sent 30 tons of essential humanitarian aid for Palestinians amid the Middle East conflict. The aid includes medicines, surgical supplies, dental products, and high-energy biscuits, distributed through UNRWA. Escalating violence has worsened food security in Gaza. The UN continues to call for a ceasefire, highlighting the deteriorating living conditions and humanitarian crisis.
title: Middle East crisis: India sends 30 tons of humanitarian aid to Palestine

description: Several BJP leaders in Jharkhand, including a sitting legislator and three former MLAs, defected due to dissatisfaction with the party's candidate list. They accuse the BJP of favoring leaders from other parties over loyal workers. Despite internal issues, the BJP remains confident in winning the upcoming assembly polls on November 13 and 20.
title: 'Reposed faith in turncoats': Discontent brews in BJP over candidates' list

description: Sunil Mittal revealed AI-generated voice cloning scams targeting executives for money transfers, emphasizing the necessity of vigilance. He highlighted the misuse of deep fakes and digital signatures, stressing the need for balancing AI's benefits with its security risks.
title: Bharti Airtel chairman Sunil Mittal has AI voice scam 'warning' for you

description: India's medal prospects took a hit as the 2026 Commonwealth Games in Glasgow will take place without sports like hockey, cricket, wrestling, and badminton. It will result in a reduced medal count when compared to the 2022 Games in Birmingham.
title: No hockey, wrestling, cricket at CWG 2026. How it hurts India
15 injured in blast at ordnance factory in Madhya Pradesh's Jabalpur

description: Several Central Reserve Police Force schools nationwide received hoax bomb threats via email, including two in Delhi and one in Hyderabad. The warnings, sent to school management, arrived late Monday night, as per sources. Authorities are investigating the situation to ensure safety and security across affected institutions.
title: Several CRPF schools, airlines receive hoax bomb threats

description: Investigators are examining whether the explosion near the CRPF school in Prashant Vihar, Rohini, is connected to former RAW officer Vikash Yadav. Yadav, targeted by pro-Khalistan groups over allegations of planning the assassination of terrorist G S Pannun, is currently under scrutiny.
title: Sleuths probe if Delhi CRPF blast linked to ex-RAW officer Vikash Yadav

description: Tesla and Elon Musk are being sued by Alcon Entertainment for allegedly using AI-created imagery resembling scenes from 'Blade Runner 2049' to promote Tesla's new robotaxi, despite being denied permission. The lawsuit seeks damages for unauthorized use and misappropriation of the film's brand.
title: Blade Runner 2024 producers sue Tesla and CEO Elon Musk; here’s why

description: India's fast-bowling duo, Jasprit Bumrah and Mohammed Shami, played crucial roles in India's historic Test series win in Australia in 2018-19. Bumrah's consistency and Shami's precision complemented each other perfectly. With both players showcasing exceptional skills, they collectively took 37 wickets, leading India to a memorable victory Down Under. India would be keeping fingers crossed for Shami to be fit for the Australia tour.
title: How Bumrah, Shami had helped India win maiden Test series in Australia

description: India's medal prospects at the 2026 Commonwealth Games in Glasgow take a hit as the organisers confirmed the exclusion of key sports like hockey, badminton, table tennis, shooting, and wrestling. These changes, part of a scaled-down event, will significantly impact India's traditionally strong performance in these disciplines.
title: CWG 2026: Hockey, wrestling, badminton, shooting among sports dropped

description: NASA’s C-130 Hercules is delivering a radar antenna reflector for the NISAR satellite to Bengaluru, India. NISAR, a joint NASA-ISRO mission, will monitor Earth's ecosystems, ice sheets, and natural hazards like earthquakes. Originally delayed, the reflector now has a special thermal coating for extra protection. The satellite will launch from India in February 2025.
title: NISAR mission: Launching in 2025, Nasa's C-130 Hercules begins journey to India

description: Elon Musk reacted humorously on X to a German magazine likening him to Hitler. Musk's repost drew support from YouTuber Naomi Seibt, who defended him against accusations and criticized the article’s portrayal. The report also highlighted Musk’s controversial views on US elections and immigration, suggesting that these stances contribute to his image as a political antagonist.
title: 'I did Nazi that coming': Elon Musk mocks Der Spiegel article with Hitler quip

description: Punjab chief minister Bhagwant Mann authorized the prosecution of Dera Sacha Sauda chief Gurmeet Ram Rahim Singh in the 2015 sacrilege cases, following the Supreme Court's decision to revive the trial. Ram Rahim is currently serving a 20-year sentence for separate rape and murder convictions.
title: Sacrilege cases: Punjab CM grants permission for prosecution of Ram Rahim

description: Counter-Intelligence Kashmir (CIK) conducted raids across multiple districts in the Kashmir Valley, targeting recruiters of the newly-formed terrorist group 'Tehreek Labaik Ya Muslim', linked to Lashkar-e-Taiba. The operations aimed to dismantle the group's recruitment network and were led by a Pakistani terrorist called Baba Hamas.
title: J&K: Counter-intel raids dismantle recruitment module of terror group

description: Despite delays, Apple CEO Tim Cook emphasizes the importance of quality, citing the success of past Apple products.  Cook asserts that Apple's AI, named Apple Intelligence, aims to be the best rather than the first. It debuts in October on newer iPhones and iPads, promising advanced features like improved Siri and image creation.
title: Apple CEO Tim Cook has these four words for the company’s AI strategy

description: New Zealand Cricket faced criticism from Indian fans for posting a map misrepresenting Jammu & Kashmir and Ladakh's borders. The post, linked to the Kiwis' travel plans for the second Test against India in Pune, was deleted after backlash. This incident follows New Zealand's eight-wicket victory over India in Bengaluru.
title: 'Showing wrong map of India': NZ Cricket slammed ahead of 2nd Test

description: Delhi's air quality deteriorated to 'very poor' with an AQI of 385. The CAQM enforced Stage II of GRAP, involving measures like mechanical sweeping and water sprinkling on roads, to address the crisis. Residents are urged to use public transport and avoid dust-generating activities to help mitigate the pollution.
title: Delhi's air quality plummets to 'very poor' category

description: Israel's military has uncovered cash and gold worth hundreds of millions of dollars in a bunker beneath Beirut's Al-Sahel Hospital, allegedly built by Hezbollah's former leader. Despite these findings, Israel will not target the hospital, instead focusing on Hezbollah’s financial assets. Lebanese officials dispute these claims.
title: Israel finds millions in cash, gold in Hezbollah’s ‘secret’ bunker; see video

description: Following the death of Hamas chief Yahya Sinwar by Israeli forces, the group opts for a five-member ruling committee based in Doha instead of appointing a single successor. This interim committee, formed after political chief Ismail Haniyeh's assassination, will lead the movement until new internal elections scheduled for March.
title: Will Hamas get a new chief after Yahya Sinwar's death?

description: During India's defeat to New Zealand in the first Test in Bengaluru, a humorous comment by Indian captain Rohit Sharma about New Zealand's Rachin Ravindra was caught on the stump mic. Despite early breakthroughs by India's bowlers, Ravindra's unbeaten 39 and Will Young’s 48 not out guided New Zealand to their first Test win in India since 1988.
title: ‘Zyada hero ban raha hai’: Rohit targets NZ batter

description: Delhi HC has urged the DU vice-chancellor to be proactive in addressing the defacement of public property by student candidates during the recent student union polls. The court emphasized the need for action, highlighting the significant cleanup costs and criticizing the administrative failure. The matter is scheduled for a hearing on October 28.
title: 'If you campaign in Rolls-Royce, you can pay to clean up DU campus'

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi will attend the Brics Summit in Kazan to discuss economic cooperation, including trade in national currencies and sustainable development. Bilateral talks with President Vladimir Putin aim to boost India-Russia trade to $100 billion by 2030, alongside cultural exchanges and digital initiatives.
title: PM Modi leaves for Russia to attend Brics summit: Full schedule

description: Somy Ali had said that she wants to meet the Bishnoi community head Devendra and not Lawrence Bishnoi because he's bewakoof (an idiot). She wants to apologise on Salman Khan's behalf and explain things to them because she doesn't want any violence or anyone to be murdered.
title: After calling Bishnoi 'bewakoof', Salman's ex-GF Somy Ali shares cryptic post

description: Kane Williamson is ruled out of the second Test against India in Pune starting on October 24. He is still recovering from a groin strain from the recent series against Sri Lanka. New Zealand leads the series 1-0 after a historic win in Bengaluru, their first on Indian soil in 36 years.
title: Kane Williamson ruled out of 2nd Test in Pune

description: India faces multiple challenges ahead of the second Test against New Zealand in Pune, with key decisions on player fitness and form. Shubman Gill's return is likely, and the team management must assess Rishabh Pant's knee injury and KL Rahul's form. Potential changes include Washington Sundar and Akash Deep to enhance flexibility and readiness for upcoming tours.
title: Plenty to ponder for Team India ahead of 2nd Test in Pune

description: Bollywood superstar Salman Khan, under threat from Lawrence Bishnoi's gang related to a 1998 poaching case, receives support from singer Mika Singh at a live performance. Mika, known for hit songs with Salman, dedicated a tribute to him. Despite heightened security, Salman remains committed to his work, currently filming 'Bigg Boss 18' and preparing for 'Sikandar' with Rashmika Mandanna.
title: Mika supports Salman Khan amid threats from Lawrence Bishnoi

description: Fintech startup Groww reported a net loss of Rs 805 crore for FY24 due to a Rs 1,340 crore tax payout from moving its parent entity to India. Despite this, Groww's operational profit rose to Rs 535 crore.
title: How Groww's tax bill & loss is a result of 'relocating' to India

description: Abhishek Bachchan praises his wife Aishwarya Rai Bachchan for being a tremendous emotional support and maintaining dignity through difficult times. He appreciates having a partner from the same industry who understands his challenges. Abhishek will next be seen as an antagonist in Sujoy Ghosh's 'King'.
title: When Abhishek praised Aishwarya Rai in front of Nimrat Kaur: 'amazing emotional support

description: Delhi HC closed contempt proceedings against Wikipedia after the platform globally removed a defamatory page. The court criticized Wikipedia for refusing to disclose user identities responsible for scandalous edits, hindering the news agency's defamation suit. The judge urged a confidential disclosure solution.
title: Delhi HC closes contempt case against Wikipedia

description: In a noteworthy case, the Supreme Court of India directed the Union government to compensate airman S P Pandey with Rs 1 lakh for a day-long detention resulting from a minor indiscipline involving overtaking a senior's vehicle at a railway crossing. The court emphasized the necessity of balanced punishment in maintaining good governance and preventing disproportionate penalties.
title: Penalised for jumping queue, airman gets Rs 1 lakh in damages

description: Seeking the death penalty for seven accused in the 2008 Malegaon blast case, the intervenor submitted that the prosecution has proved its case beyond reasonable doubt. Despite changes in regime and hostile civilian witnesses, police witnesses supported the case, affirming trust in the judicial system.
title: Malegaon case proved beyond doubt, accused deserve death: Intervener

description: A traders' body in Chamoli had issued a resolution requiring 15 Muslim families to leave Khansar by December 31. This stance was retracted following condemnation from AIMIM president Asaduddin Owaisi. The traders claimed the resolution was misinterpreted and aimed only at those without proper police verification. Authorities stressed maintaining peace and harmony.
title: Chamoli traders drop diktat asking minorities to leave
What changes as India reverts to 2020 LAC patrolling terms?

description: The Supreme Court has dismissed ex-Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal's plea to quash summons in a defamation case tied to his comments on PM Modi's educational qualifications. This aligns with a previous rejection faced by AAP leader Sanjay Singh, ensuring legal proceedings continue.
title: No SC relief, Kejriwal to face defamation trial over Modi-degree jibes
Sanjauli mosque panel starts razing structure’s illegal parts

description: New Zealand cricket teams celebrated historic victories as the men's team clinched their first Test win in India in 36 years, and the women's team secured their inaugural ICC Women's T20 World Cup title. Key performances by Rachin Ravindra and Amelia Kerr were instrumental in these wins, earning them 'Player of the Match' honours.
title: 'Epic': Williamson reacts as NZ teams seal historic wins

description: Sanju Samson discussed his disappointment about being dropped from the T20 World Cup final lineup, despite being ready to play. He appreciated captain Rohit Sharma's effort to explain the decision before the toss, which strengthened their bond. Although Samson missed the World Cup, he shone in the subsequent T20I series against Bangladesh.
title: 'I know you're cursing me in your mind': Rohit to Samson

description: Lieutenant Governor VK Saxena shares images of toxic froth in Yamuna, questioning those accountable for its cleanup. AAP accuses BJP of using old photos for political gain, while Congress criticizes AAP for failing to address pollution. Allegations arise over industrial waste from neighboring states, with Delhi government initiating antifoam measures to combat pollution.
title: Yamuna’s frothing triggers three-way political tussle in Delhi

description: Ajay Wankhede, an army personnel from Ajni, murdered his girlfriend Jyotsna Akre after she pressured him for marriage. He buried her body in a forest near Nagpur and discarded her cellphone to mislead investigators. Police eventually cracked the case and arrested Wankhede.
title: Army man commits 'Drishyam' style murder, GF's body found buried in cement

description: The All India Consumer Products Distributors Federation has lodged a complaint with the CCI, accusing quick commerce companies like Zomato's Blinkit, Swiggy, and Zepto of predatory pricing. These practices are making it hard for traditional retailers to compete, affecting the livelihoods of 400,000 retail distributors.
title: India's top retail group files complaint against Blinkit, Zepto & Swiggy

description: A 40-year-old man in Bhopal's Sunder Nagar set himself on fire after his wife did not return home for Karva Chauth despite his requests. He suffered 70% burn injuries and was declared dead at Hamidia Hospital. Police have registered a case.
title: Wife not home on Karva Chauth, man dies by suicide in Bhopal

description: A leopard attacked a group of picnickers in Khitauli village, MP's Shahdol district, injuring three people, including a woman and an off-duty police officer who sustained severe head injuries. The incident occurred when the group, spotting the leopard, inadvertently provoked it from the bushes.
title: Picnickers in MP call out to leopard ‘aa jaa’, it rips into them

description: The US has blacklisted over two dozen entities from Pakistan, China, and the UAE, banning them from acquiring US goods and technologies. The Commerce Department accuses these entities of violating export controls, supporting weapons programs, and evading sanctions. Nine Pakistani entities allegedly acted as fronts, while six Chinese entities advanced military projects.
title: Tech trade sanctions: US blocks Chinese, Pakistani companies over military ties

description: The BJP's initial list of candidates for Maharashtra's assembly election, featuring prominent figures like Devendra Fadnavis and Chandrashekhar Bawankule, aims to balance Maratha and OBC representation following the Jat-OBC model used in Haryana. This strategy addresses past electoral setbacks due to Maratha reservation agitation.
title: Marathas vs OBCs: How BJP is trying Haryana-type social engineering in Maharashtra

description: Dharmaraj Kashyap ditched his path towards a medical career, lured by gangsters' social media bravado, and became involved in crime, culminating in his involvement in Baba Siddique's murder. His brother Anurag, now regretful, reveals connections to the Bishnoi gang and failed efforts to keep Dharmaraj on the right path.
title: 'Bishnoi his idol': Shooter who 'killed' Baba Siddique aced class 10, then veered to crime
